<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Burma-Releases     07-08 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Burma-Releases,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Authorities Free 390 People Arrested In Riots</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities have released 390 people
arrested in student riots in March and June, the state radio said.
   The broadcast said those freed Thursday included 229 students,
147 civilians and 14 government employees. It said 240 people were
freed in the national capital of Rangoon and the others in the
cities of Pegu, Prome and Moulmein.
   The broadcast said some people were freed unconditionally and
others on bail. It did not say how many people had been arrested,
but it said releases will continue.
   In the most recent riots in Rangoon on June 21, university
students demanded that the government legalize student unions and
free students detained in earlier protests.
   Authorities said nine people were killed when thousands of
demonstrators clashed with riot police. Seventy-seven people were
arrested in connection with that riot, they said.
   Authorities closed most educational institutions and imposed a
curfew until Aug. 17.
</TEXT>
