<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--50-YearNudist     07-08 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--50-Year Nudist,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Hasn't Worn Anything Since He Was Born</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A carpenter in the village of
Kalampang says he has never worn anything but what he was wearing
when he was born 50 years ago, the newspaper Kompas reported.
   A reporter found Aco, who goes by one name, nude last Sunday at
his home in the village 1,000 miles northeast of the capital, the
paper said Thursday.
   ``My body will itch very badly if I wear any clothes or
sarong,'' Kompas quoted Aco as saying.
   It quoted a neighbor as saying that when Aco was a baby, he
protested and cried whenever his mother tried to put clothes on him.
   A doctor checked the man this week and found him physically and
mentally healthy, the paper said.
