<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--ElvisWall     07-08 0172</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Elvis Wall,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Car Bashes Graceland Wall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An out-of-control car smashed through the
wall surrounding Elvis Presley's Graceland manor, and a guard later
stood watch to keep fans from carrying off broken bricks,
authorities said.
   Detrich Michelle Hardy, 21, was charged with failure to maintain
proper control of her vehicle and driving without a license in the
accident early Thursday, the Memphis Police Department reported.
   ``Usually, most people wait for the place to open in the morning
to get access to the property,'' Graceland spokesman Todd Morgan
joked.
   Hardy and a male companion were speeding down Elvis Presley
Boulevard when they ``lost control for some reason, took a sharp
left and drove through the stone wall that is in front of
Graceland,'' Morgan said.
   The car ended up in the large yard in front of the white house.
There were no injuries, Morgan said. ``We've had a guard on the
wall all day today to keep pieces of the wall from going home as
souvenirs,'' he added.
</TEXT>
