<1ST_LINE>r w PM-Airliner-Transcript     07-08 0312</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Airliner-Transcript,300</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Airliner Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Pentagon Shows Iranians Responded To Warship Warnings In Past</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Pentagon says the record of a radio
encounter between an Iranian F-14 and a U.S. cruiser shows that
Iranian aircraft respond to warnings from U.S. warships in the
Persian Gulf, unlike Iran Air flight 655, which was shot down last
Sunday.
   The Iranian A300 Airbus did not reply to seven warnings
broadcast by the warship which shot it down, the USS Vincennes, and
five from another American vessel in the area, the USS John H.
Sides, said Pentagon spokesman Dan Howard.
   To demonstrate that ignoring such warnings was unusual, Howard
released a previously classified conversation between an Iranian
F-14 fighter and the Leahy class guided missile cruiser USS Halsey.
   The conversation took place last Saturday, the day before the
Airbus was shot down with 290 civilians aboard.
   HALSEY: ``Unidentified warship bearing 3:10 speed 400 knots,
altitude 2,000 feet, you are approaching an American warship,
operating in international waters, bearing 1:29, 26 nautical miles
from you. Request you to establish communications and identify
yourself and state your intentions.''
   IRANIAN F-14: ``Roger. An Iranian. We will place you about 5
nautical miles.''
   HALSEY: From U.S. naval warship, say again.''
   IRANIAN F-14: ``We want to place your warship at about 10
nautical miles.''
   HALSEY: ``Roger, out.''
   IRANIAN F-14: ``Roger.''
   Howard said the text was ``the sum total of the transcript. The
Iranian aircraft went away.''
   ``He identified himself and established where he was. Now the
events worked out. There was no hostile intent. These aircraft were
tracked.''
   Last Thursday, the commander of U.S. forces in the Persian Gulf,
Marine Corps Gen. George B. Crist, cited another instance, in which
an Iranian F-4 came ``a little close'' to a U.S. ship ``and our
ship challenged him. He said, `I'm on my way to engage an Iraqi.''
</TEXT>
