<HEAD>Boy Killed, 50 Injured In Grenade Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hand grenade exploded at a
singing contest, killing a 12-year-old boy and wounding 50 other
people, mostly children, police said today.
   A constabulary report from southern Basilan province said most
of the injured were children watching the contest in the town plaza
of Isabela, the provincial capital, late Thursday.
   Investigators said the grenade was hurled from the back of the
stage onto the crowd below. No suspects have been arrested in the
incident, which occurred on the eve of Isabela's annual feastday.
   Renegade members of the Moro National Liberation Front, a Moslem
rebel group demanding autonomy in the southern Philippines, are
known to operate in the area and have been blamed for attacks on
nearby towns in the past months.
   Basilan is located 18 miles south of here and about 560 miles
from Manila.
