<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0448</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Dump Rain On South, Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms moved slowly across the western Texas Panhandle
early today and dumped up to 6 inches of rain on the southern
Plains, while heavy rains also drenched parts of Colorado,
Minnesota and Wyoming.
   Hail pounded parts of eastern Colorado Thursday and a tornado
was reported in eastern Kit Carson County northeast of Burlington.
No injuries or damage were reported.
   In Texas, flooding was reported Thursday night across Lynn
County with many roads under water; a few residences were flooded
at Ropesville; and 2 inches of water drenched City Hall.
   A cold front spread from central and southern Minnesota to
southeast Wyoming, into northeast and central Colorado, and
scattered thunderstorms along its way. Three to 4 inches of rain
fell on parts of northeast Colorado.
   In southwest Minnesota, nearly 2 inches of rain fell on Marshall
and around an inch at Granite Falls and Montevideo.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included more than 3{ inches at Reese Air Force Base near Lubbock,
Texas.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
through southern Florida, along the western half of the Gulf of
Mexico coast, in eastern Texas, through inland portions of North
Carolina, across west central Wisconsin into southeast Minnesota,
over central Colorado and central Arizona.
   High temperatures were forecast in the upper 80s and the 90s
throughout much of the nation; near 100 over the Ohio Valley; near
110 degrees through the desert Southwest; in the mid 80s through
Maine, northern Minnesota, from the Dakotas across the Texas
Panhandle and over eastern Colorado; and in the 70s and 80s along
the California coast.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 42
degrees at Lake Yellowstone, Wyo., to 99 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 72 fair; Boston 71 partly cloudy; Buffalo 72
hazy; Charleston, S.C. 70 fair; Cincinnati 73 hazy; Cleveland 74
hazy; Detroit 78 hazy; Miami 78 partly cloudy; New York 71 fair;
Philadelphia 74 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 74 hazy; Portland, Maine
66 foggy; Washington 77 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 57 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 75 fair; Denver 60
partly cloudy; Des Moines 74 fair; Indianapolis 76 hazy; Kansas
City 75 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 75 fair; Nashville 75 fair; New
Orleans 76 partly cloudy; St. Louis 77 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 71 fair; Anchorage 59 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 87 fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 99 fair; Salt Lake City
71 fair; San Diego 66 partly cloudy; San Francisco 53 fair; Seattle
61 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 77 partly cloudy; Toronto 72 hazy.
