<FILEID>AP-NR-07-08-88 1010EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-MechamAide     07-08 0218</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Mecham Aide,0221</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Aide to Former Arizona Governor Named to Hollywood Chamber of
Commerce Job</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A top legislative aide for former Arizona
Gov. Evan Mecham has been named director of development for the
Hollywood Chamber of Commerce.
   In the new position, Donna Carlson will be in charge of the
chamber's participation in the Hollywood redevelopment program and
its entertainment industry-related events, work as an ombudswoman
and try to generate membership.
   Ms. Carlson was the legislative liaison for the Republican
governor but resigned before he was forced from office. She said
she received a death threat for her willingness to testify before a
grand jury investigating Mecham. Mecham's handling of the
investigation into the threat formed the basis of one count of his
impeachment and removal from office.
   Ms. Carlson served for eight years as a member of the Arizona
House of Representatives. After losing a bid for Congress in 1982,
she moved to California in 1984 to set up a branch office for an
Arizona company that manufactures road equipment.
   She returned to Arizona two years later to become executive
director of a Phoenix-based trade association, then returned to
public service to work for Mecham.
   In October, she attributed her departure to frustration over an
inability to get clear signals from her bosses.
</TEXT>
