<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--RapBodyguard     07-08 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Rap Bodyguard,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ex-Bodyguard for Run-D.M.C. Pleads Guilty to Voluntary
Manslaughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRESNO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former bodyguard for the rap music group
Run-DMC has pleaded guilty to involuntary manslaughter in the death
of a man at a concert two years ago.
   Garfield Brown had been scheduled for a preliminary hearing
Thursday in Municipal Court in connection with the death of Alex
Baldwin, 21.
   Police said several fights broke out during a Run-DMC concert at
Selland Arena in this city 200 miles north of Los Angeles on Aug.
15, 1986, and Brown and two other bodyguards left the stage to help
restore order.
   Brown was charged with throwing Baldwin to the concrete floor
and kicking him. Baldwin died of head injuries two weeks later, and
Brown was arrested in New York City.
   He will be sentenced in Superior Court on Aug. 1. The maximum
sentence he could receive is four years in prison.
</TEXT>
