<2ND_LINE>PM-India-Gas Leak, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0615,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Precede NEW DELHI</HEAD>
<HEAD>13 Die After Inhaling Carbon Dioxide</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: UPDATES thruout with official saying carbon dioxide blamed
for deaths.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>KARNAL, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirteen farmers died after they went into
wells contaminated with carbon dioxide, a government official said
today.
   Kartar Singh Bhoria, deputy commissioner in Karnal in the
northern state of Haryana, said the deaths occurred Thursday and
today in six villages near Karnal.
   He said all of the farmers were stricken after they climbed into
the wells to start up underground pumps for irrigating rice
paddies. Tests showed the wells to be filled with carbon dioxide,
he said.
   The colorless and odorless gas was believed formed underground
because of radical climate changes over the past year. Last year
the region suffered severe drought.
   Karnal is 72 miles north of New Delhi.
   The Press Trust of India said other villages were warned of
possible danger.
   Government officials urged farmers to lower burning candles or
lamps into the well to check for gas before entering the wells
themselves. The flame will be extinguished if carbon dioxide gas is
present, they said.
</TEXT>
