<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--Drought-Conservation     07-08 0115</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Drought-Conservation,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lyng Discounts Grain Harvesting Rumors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Farmers are not authorized to harvest grain
from set-aside and conservation land that has been approved for
haying or livestock grazing, Agriculture Secretary Richard E. Lyng
said Friday.
   A statement issued by his office said that ``current rumors that
such authorization is imminent are false'' and that ``the
requirement is still in effect that a protective cover be placed on
land out of production'' under the programs.
   The Agriculture Department has authorized farmers in designated
counties _ 1,934 in 37 states as of Friday _ to cut hay or ``green
chop'' the protective cover for use as feed. It cannot be harvested
for grain.
</TEXT>
