<HEAD>Air Force Plane Crash Kills Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An air force plane crashed and
exploded Friday as it tried an emergency landing shortly after
takeoff in southern Brazil, killing five people and injuring four
others, TV Globo said.
   The Brazilian-made plane had just lifted off with nine crewmen
aboard for a test run at the Aerospace Technological Center in Sao
Jose dos Campos, 275 miles west of Rio de Janeiro, when it
developed engine trouble, the network's report said. It attributed
its information to the Air Force Ministry.
   When the plane tried to make an emergency landing, one of its
wing tips hit the runway, setting off an explosion that killed five
of the crewmen and injured the other four, the TV report said.
   Four of those aboard were military personnel and five were
technicians, the report said.
   Comment was unavailable from the Air Force Ministry, which was
closed. An official at the Aerospace Technological Center confirmed
an accident had occurred but said he could not give details.
