<1ST_LINE>r f PM-AutoRecall     07-08 0194</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Auto Recall,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>389,000 Renault Alliance, Encore Cars Need Repairs, Adjustments</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. plans to send redesigned pressure
caps to owners of 240,000 1985-87 Renault Alliance and Encore cars
to prevent rupture of a passenger compartment heater component.
   Owners of the 1985-87 vehicles will be mailed pressure caps,
revised to prevent rupture of the heater core due to severe engine
overheating, Chrysler said Thursday in a statement.
   The heater core, a component located in the passenger
compartment where air is heated, would spray steam and hot water on
the driver's legs if it ruptured, Chrysler spokeswoman Karen
Stewart said.
   Chrysler said it knew of 39 incidents of injury due to heater
core rupture.
   In a separate notification, Chrysler said it would recall about
149,000 1983-84 Alliances and Encores equipped with drivers'
rocker-recliner seats for adjustment of the seat bracket.
   Stronger brackets will be made available this fall to prevent
the front attachments of the seat adjuster from separating and
allowing the seat to tip backward, the statement said.
   The company said it received about 50 reports of seat adjuster
attachment failure on 1983 and 1984 cars, including three minor
injuries.
</TEXT>
