<2ND_LINE>PM-Bridgestone President,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bridgestone Names American Chief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bridgestone USA Inc. has chosen James P.
McMann as the first American president of the Tokyo-based company,
officials said.
   McMann, a 35-year veteran of Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. who has
been executive vice president of Bridgestone USA Inc. since
December 1986, will step into the position Aug. 1, officials said
Thursday.
   He succeeds Norihiro Takeuchi, who will now serve as senior vice
president for business planning.
   McCann served as managing director in Malaysia for five years
and as president of Goodyear Japan for three years. He retired from
the company in 1985 as vice president of Asia Pacific Goodyear
International Corp.
   Bridgestone, which plans to move its headquarters from Torrance,
Calif., to Nashville by Aug. 1, recently merged with Firestone and
now manages and operates Firestone's worldwide holdings.
   Bridgestone is the No. 1 tiremaker in Japan and the third
largest worldwide. It produces most types of tires and industrial
rubber and chemical products in five countries.
</TEXT>
