<1ST_LINE>r f BC-EEC-Japan     07-08 0132</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Japan,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Imposes Dumping Duty On Japanese Printers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Economic Community
announced Friday a provisional dumping duty on Japanese daisy-wheel
computer printers.
   The action follows the decision in late May to slap a similar
duty on the makers of dot matrix printers, the other major category
of computer printers.
   According to Friday's announcement by the European Commission, a
duty of 43.2 percent will be imposed on the daisy-wheel printers
made by all companies except Tokyo Electric Co. Ltd. and Tokyo Juki
Industrial Co. Ltd., whose printers will be taxed at a lower rate
of 12.4 percent.
   These rates compare with a duty of 33.4 percent charged on dot
matrix printers made by seven companies and duties ranging from 4.8
to 22.4 percent on eight others.
</TEXT>
