<HEAD>Reagan To Make Nomination To Export-Import Bank Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan plans to nominate Arizona
banker Richard C. Houseworth to a four-year term on the board of
directors of the Export-Import Bank, the White House announced
Friday.
   Houseworth, 60, who has been with the Arizona Bank in Phoenix
since 1955 as a vice president and consultant, would succeed
