<NOTE>Eds: Updates thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London Stock Exchange jumped Friday,
helped by bullish news on the U.S. economy and renewed strength in
the dollar.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 21.7
points, or 1.2 percent, to 1,877.2.
