<HEAD>New World Entertainment Puts Marvel Comics Up for Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marvel Entertainment Group, the comic book
home of Spiderman, the Incredible Hulk and Captain America, has
been put up for sale by New World Entertainment Ltd., the company
announced Thursday.
   New World, the movie and toy company that acquired Marvel for a
reported $40 million to $50 million in November 1986, said it would
sell all or part of Marvel Entertainment Group.
